07/06/2005
KARLOVO, Bulgaria -- Army chief General Nikola Kolev announced on Monday (6 June) that the country has been invited to participate in a UN mission in Iraq. 
Sofia has been asked to send a small unit to protect and secure a UN office there. 
The operation would be co-financed by the UN, the international coalition in Iraq, and Bulgaria. 
(Sega, Novinar - 07/06/05)
